If the user enters a `y` value that&#39;s divisible by 10, then `z` will also be divisible by `10`. Then, when you set `m=(z%10);`, `m` is set to 0. Doing `y % m` in such a situation is a division by 0 error.

Maybe consider first checking to make sure `m` isn&#39;t 0? 
```c
if(m == 0 || y%m==0)
{
  total++;
}
```

